<p>What the activities of survivalists, preppers, and those like Roscoe Bartlett highlight is a feeling among many Americans, not all of whom respond in this manner (of preparing), that the status quo is intolerable and that it will end. So, the question is, can we keep going on like this? I think that as long as MOST people have jobs and can afford massive quantities of &#8220;stuff&#8221; that it WILL go on. It is not until the gravy train ends that real change will occur. Just how our neighbors respond to that is what is in doubt in the minds of preppers. There can be a positive outcome, and most certainly will be, but the path to get there and to convince our neighbors that the quality of this future shall be better than the quantity of our present, is a daunting one, to say the least, and hiding out in a hole in the woods somewhere doesn&#8217;t help.</p>
